Class URLInputIterator

              +--xxl.io.URLInputIterator
public class URLInputIterator
extends InputIterator

This class provides an iterator that depends on a given URL. It iterates over the objects that are read out of the URL's input stream. A converter is used in order to read out the serialized objects.

This class implements only a few constructors. These constructers create an new input iterator that depends on an input stream for reading from the connection to the given URL.

Example usage (1). 

     // catch MalformedURLExceptions
     try {
         // create a new URLInputIterator with ...
         URLInputIterator it = new URLInputIterator(
             // a factory method that creates KPEs with 2 dimensions
             new Function() {
                 public Object invoke () {
                     return new xxl.spatial.KPE(2);
                 }
             },
             // a given URL
             new URL("http://www.mathematik.uni-marburg.de/DBS/xxl/rr_small.bin")
         );

         // print all elements of the queue
         while(it.hasNext())
             System.out.println(it.next());
     }
     catch (java.net.MalformedURLException mue) {
         System.out.println("The given URL is malformed.");
     }

See Also:

Constructor Detail

URLInputIterator

public URLInputIterator(Converter converter,
                        URL url,
                        int bufferSize)
Constructs a new URLInputIterator that depends on the specified URL and uses the specified converter in order to read out the serialized objects. An internal buffer of size bufferSize is used for the URL input.
Parameters:
converter - the converter that is used for reading out the serialized objects of this iteration.
url - the URL that contains the serialized objects of this iteration.
bufferSize - the size of the buffer that is used for the URL input

URLInputIterator

public URLInputIterator(Function newObject,
                        URL url,
                        int bufferSize)
Constructs a new URLInputIterator that depends on the specified URL and uses the specified factory method to initialize an object of this iteration before the URL is read out. When using this constructor the objects of the iteration must implement the Convertable interface. An internal buffer of size bufferSize is used for the URL input.
This constructor is equivalent to the call of new URLInputIterator(new ConvertableConverter(newObject), url, bufferSize).
Parameters:
newObject - a factory method that is used for initializing an object of this iteration before the URL is read out.
url - the URL that contains the serialized objects of this iteration.
bufferSize - the size of the buffer that is used for the URL input
